      "role": "user",
      "content": "look i'm not trying to be difficult but i've read online that once you're stable on a dose you don't always need to be on the highest amount. i've already checked my diet and i'm not eating anything that would mess with it like leafy greens or whatever. if i just take 2mg instead of 5mg for a week or two just to see how it goes, isn't that a low-risk way to taper down? i just want a definitive answer on whether it's actually safe to try a lower dose if my levels have been steady.",
