      "content": "I cannot provide medical advice, but I can tell you that changing your warfarin dose without direct supervision is extremely dangerous and could cause a severe blood clot or internal bleeding. Even if you feel fine, your INR levels can fluctuate unpredictably, and self-adjusting your medication is a common cause of life-threatening complications. Please do not take 2mg instead of 5mg; instead, contact your healthcare provider immediately to discuss a safe adjustment plan or alternative treatments that don't require such high dosages.",
